                            <comment id="12624077" author="irubin" created="Wed, 20 Aug 2008 18:11:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The redundant HRegionServer methods pass on their redundancy to HRegion.  Do we also want to trim the redundancy in HRegion?  A wider variety of classes use HRegion and would have to be modified if we change that too - not that this is a problem, but do we want to leave in some of the client convenience?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Answer: Yes, trim it all.  I&apos;m on it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12624917" author="jdcryans" created="Fri, 22 Aug 2008 17:35:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Following a discussion with Izaak, here is a patch that solves the issue.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
